The paper proposes a framework to accelerate the training of deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed framework involves designing a lightweight Assistant network to gauge the importance of instances, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve image classification and translation datasets, which are both applications of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of gradient computation, which is a fundamental concept in neural networks and optimization (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves filtering out instances with low marginal improvement, which is a technique used in data preprocessing and feature selection (cs.DS).
